node.text: I’ve never flown a drone before in my years of filming and that all changed when @djiglobal reached out to me to test their new product the “#DJImini2”. Legit was the most fun and easiest thing I’ve ever used to shoot.. @christian_habberstad & myself had endless creative abilities with this one 🥳.. Much love @djiglobal nobody can compete with your guys design!!

node.text: Now days I try to make my post a bit less personal.. But, today Is an Interesting chapter for me. This day makes 10 years without my mother. It really seems like time has moved so slow but, recalling her voice and warmth in my memory makes it feel as just yesterday evening I had her in my presence.. I often remembered that saying “time heals all wounds”. My 16 year old brain would repeat “One day it will be 1 year from now, One day it will be 5 years from now, & finally the day has arrived that it’s 10 years from now”.. Time & Space makes our consciousness a dynamic place; things do get easier. Day after day.. year after year, I promise ♥. Sweet enough my mother left me a note on her death bed. Reading it made me realize whatever it is we lose, we seem to find ourself there as well; Between our tears & laughter, our war & peace, the silence and noise, the inner world & outer world there seems to be a common reoccurring theme of each breath we take.. Somewhere beneath it all is the monomaniac flow of presence that life experiences itself as through you & I. It seems as every possible outcome of experience in this life brings each individual being home to the same realization.. & that is Love.. There has never been someone who hasn’t loved. Whether selfishly or fully, it is our true nature.. Blindfolds on or off it’s the algorithm of your deepest self. ♥
